net.akami.mask.alteration

Interface IOCalculationModifier<T>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    CalculationAlteration<T>, java.lang.Comparable<CalculationAlteration>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DegreeUnit, GradientUnit

    public interface IOCalculationModifier<T>
extends CalculationAlteration<T>
    An IOModifier checks whether a given expression needs to be formatted or not.
    When required, it replaces the input by its formatted version. The modifications can be applied before or after performing a calculation.
    For instance, the angle unit modifier will check before performing a trigonometric operation whether it must convert the input to radians before proceeding. On the other hand, the fraction modifier will check after performing any operation whether the merge must be transformed to a fraction or not.
